
[1]shriek

   SHRIEK, v.i. [L. ruga, wrinkled, rugo, to bray.] To utter a sharp
   shrill cry; to scream; as in sudden fright, in horror or anguish.

   At this she shriek'd aloud. Dryden.

   It was the owl that shriek'd. Shak.

   SHRIEK, n. A sharp shrill outcry or scream, such as is produced by
   sudden anger or extreme anguish.
